Bitcoin vs Kaspa BPS

I've been thinking about $KAS 10 BPS & how impressive this really is compared to Bitcoin's average of 1 block every 10 minutes. I created a visualisation for this.

We need to show the space just how impressive this blockchain is. Kaspa community, I'm counting on you.

The visualisation below is sped up by 2x, so it takes 5 minutes for the orange (Bitcoin) block to move from left to right. In that time, 6,000 green dots which represent Kaspa blocks move from left to right.

Since many people missed out on their opportunity at 25k #Bitcoin, the biggest question I've gotten after the rise is will we see below 30k again?

Here's a reminder:

We've just broken through 8-month resistance at yellow layer 1!

Bitcoin now prefers higher prices like 39 and 48k.

We have had, and continue to have too many people eyeing the 2019 cycle which looks nothing like our current one. Copy-pasting the black swan right on top.

If you bet too long against Bitcoin, you're going to be on the wrong side of history.

Price does like to retest primary levels, so it is likely we see a revisit of Level 1 at some point, which is priced at $31,919.

The problem is, you'll be too scared to buy then too.

If you bought between the bottom layer (red) and layer 1 (yellow) you're in a great position for the cycle!

📢📰 #CryptoNews from last week🗣️🌐
(30th Oct'23 to 5th Nov'23) #MonkNews
Make sound investment strategy by keeping updated with the latest updates from the world of #Crypto

🗞️PayPal receives approval to offer crypto services in the United Kingdom.
🗞️ Thailand's second-largest bank, Kasikornbank, acquires local crypto exchange.
🗞️UK to regulate crypto in 2024.
🗞️Circle will no longer support stablecoin minting for consumer accounts
🗞️SEC charges SafeMoon crypto token & its executives with fraud. Arrests founders John Karony, Kyle Nagy & Thomas Smith.
🗞️Swiss Bank St.Galler Kantonalbank to offer Bitcoin and Ethereum custody services.
🗞️Elon Musk says none of his companies "will ever create a crypto token.
🗞️X (Twitter) now valued at $19 billion, Fortune reports.
🗞️Federal Reserve pauses interest rate hikes, remains at 5.25% - 5.50%.
🗞️Swiss Bank St.Galler Kantonalbank to offer Bitcoin and Ethereum custody services, faces maximum sentence of 115 years in prison, judge sets sentencing date for March 28, 2024.
🗞️Bitcoin has a larger market cap than Bank of America and Bank of China combined.
🗞️#BlackRock's Bitcoin #ETF might have trading support of heavyweights like Jane Street, Jump and Virtu
🗞️#Coinbase crypto futures for retail US traders goes live, includes 'nano' Bitcoin trading
🗞️In October, MicroStrategy acquired an additional 155 #BTC for $5.3 million and now holds 158,400 BTC
🗞️ProShares launches Ether futures ETF for crypto bears
🗞️US Supreme Court takes up Coinbase arbitration dispute
🗞️#FTX wants to sell $744m worth of Grayscale, Bitwise assets
🗞️#Solana has announced a partnership with Amazon Web Services. #Solana nodes are now available for quick deployment on AWS.
🗞️Coin98 announced that it changed the project name to Ninety Eight $C98.
🗞️24.842 million $APT will unlock on November 12, 2023.
🗞️Hashkey, a licensed exchange in Hong Kong, officially launched an APP for retail trading today
🗞️The Dubai Financial Services Authority (DFSA) has approved the use of 💎#TON and 🪙#XRP for the Dubai International Financial Centre (DIFC).

#cryptomarket #CryptoCommunity #Cryptocurency #cryptocurrencies #crypto #CryptoTrend #bitcoin #BTC #SOL #ETH #ADA

Everyone and their mothers are waiting for that 100k #Bitcoin.

Many say they won't sell, but honestly, many will.

That magic number will be a great ceiling to surpass, but many will think that #BTC can't go any further.

This next cycle is going to melt faces away. 

It's going to surprise a lot of people,

Those who will sell at 100k will FOMO at higher prices.

After #Bitcoin Spot ETFs,

We will still need to see inflows; 

That will determine the institutional demand for #Bitcoin. 

And if, for some reason, there is not sufficient demand, 

We will have to wait until the halving to see a further increase.

Time will tell; you should be prepared.

Sine waves are one of the clearest ways to show the cycles of my Halving Cycles Theory for #Bitcoin.

Now more than ever, it is apparent which cycle we are following, sights are locked on 2015 - 2018.

The 2019 bearish bias has now all been but extinguished, and if you've been following BitTime, you would have known that we should be rallying at this point.

BitTime says that cycles are extremely similar when they alternate, but here you can see that all cycles resemble each other, centered around the date of the first and second halving:

- Nov 28th, 2012

- July 9th, 2016

The "this time is different' people will be back with a vengeance soon, with ETFs looming.

But remember, it's not different until it is.

And if you think this way, you'll have a much better chance of being successful.

Everything is right on track.

Cars don't drive drunk, people drive drunk.

On December 31st, 2022, I made a simple #Bitcoin observation (see next post)

Fears of 10-12k and a recession were at their highest, but data said Bitcoin was due for a great 2023.

I said that it was time to return to the median, which gives balance between tops and bottoms.

We have had some wild predictions this year...

From new ATHs, to new cycle lows and black swans.

But so far it's ended up so simple, at 16.5k Bitcoin was undervalued, and now it is back to fair value.

I still think Bitcoin has some room to run over fair value before it establishes time around it next year.

"This time is different" is your worst enemy.

When I first learned about #Bitcoin, 

I couldn't stop reading about it for months. 

It changed how I thought about everything. 

I can't believe Bitcoin isn't worth more than $500k yet.

It's surprising how many people are okay with the way things are now. 

If they're not moved by the problems with our current money system, 

what will make them see what Bitcoin can do?

Lots of people are like zombies, not really thinking about what's going on. 

How can we get them to wake up and see the opportunities?

Prepare yourselves for an unforgettable journey coming soon.

40k? 50k? 100k? 150k?

 Feels like a true shift in sentiment.

Maybe I'm right, maybe not.

I will continue with dollar-cost averaging, just like every day.

The potential upside for purchasing power is unimaginable!

The inevitable win for BTC is upon us.

MVRV has now helped me sell my #Bitcoin at 54k in April 2021, and buy back in at 16.5k in Nov 2022.
(See posts below)

But so far, I've had to be a little creative to be able to do this.

I want to show you a way I think will help to make it even more accurate, by applying a 50-day moving average.

This smooths out the topping points and makes it much easier to determine when to act.

The top line is set at 5.8, and if you take a look at the exit prices, most people would be more than happy with the outcomes.

It also gives us a better bottom point. If you wait for a cross under -0.2 value, you could secure the green prices shown.

Again, much better than just waiting for the red or green zones.

MVRV still has a long way to go until it reaches a tipping point, and as always, best to use data from many sources to confirm!

#Bitcoin is ruled by time, centered around the date of the first halving, November 28th.

So what typically happens during this time?

Usually, a drop in price, which Bitcoin has been avoiding thus far.

In all cycles, not just the ones I have shown here, Bitcoin has rallied in quarter 4 of Green Year, followed by a drop into the year's end.

Then, price makes a secondary surge into the beginning of Blue Year which typically ends around Dec - Feb, followed by an additional sideways period until the second early top in Blue Year quarter 3.

The window for a larger drop is closing in, and the early blue year rise awaits!

BTC and #Crypto markets update

Today, $BTC hit two of the key areas I identified in my previous post from yesterday. We are back within the channel again, resting at the lower trendline. This is not a good sign for the bulls because this trendline has been hit way too many times now, which makes it super weak to act as support. Now we watch how the price acts here and if it finds support. If it does not find support here, we are looking at the two previous areas I have identified. If it does find support, we will have to see how price acts at the upper trendline of the channel which now acts as resistance. 

As I have said before, November can be super volatile (hence my strategy to DCA next few months). Having a long term strategy is helpful when we want to stay in the game long term! 

#BTC #BITCOIN #ETH #Ethereum $ETH $SOL $BNB $ADA $KDA $DAO #Cryptocurrency #NFT #NFTs

#Bitcoin Price Report 

1. We rejected exactly from the level marked as per our last price update.

2. Early Tuesday saw a Monday Low sweep but things get ugly below it if we close there. Shorts were added on Monday as OI went up and perp CVD decreased while spot CVD showed no movement

3. We have an nPOC above us and the previous range VaH as support below. This will one of the most important levels to keep an eye on before daily close

4. The level highlighted in golden box below is where market buyers chased price and caused the pump to mark our current high. This was a spot led pump and there has not been very high spot selling since then so will be interesting to see if buyers defend their entry level there

5. CPI today so market can be volatile, entry can be taken post the news from either side if the trigger is given by the market Gods.

Updated Hyblock Heatmaps and Liquidation Levels for BTC, ETH, SOL, LINK & TRB

Bitcoin has been in an uninterrupted uptrend since the big pump on October 23rd.

It's worth watching the video below but before,

Ask yourself this, 

Was Jason Lowery (Softwar) a spook that infiltrated the #BTC community just to sell a book?

or 

Was He literally right about 99% of what he said?

As we move forward in this age of technological advancement, 

I wholeheartedly believe that the acquisition and ownership of #Bitcoin is crucial for national security,

It should be safeguarded by both the 1st and 2nd Amendments of the United States Constitution. 

The First Amendment, 

Which protects freedom of speech, press and religion, 

Plays an essential role in ensuring that citizens have the right to speak freely about the importance of Bitcoin.

In the digital age, 

Where data is the new "gold", cryptographic assets like #Bitcoin represent the epitome of free speech, 

An un-censorable form of expression that transcends borders.

The Second Amendment, 

Which protects an individual's right to keep and bear arms, is equally vital when applied to the concept of "true property." 

Just as one has the right to defend their physical property, so should they have the right to defend their digital assets. 

While firearms might be the conventional means to protect physical property, cryptographic security measures serve as the "digital arms" to protect #Bitcoin. 

Digital security is the 21st-century equivalent of personal defense, and just as one has the right to bear arms for self-defense, 

One should also have the right to employ cryptographic defenses to safeguard their #Bitcoin.

The essence of both amendments can be distilled into the broader right to personal freedom and security. 

Failure to integrate #Bitcoin into our understanding of rights could be detrimental, leaving the nation vulnerable to the ramifications of centralized financial systems and undermining the freedom and security upon which America was built.

Worth watching. 👇

#Bitcoin is:
1) cash
2) a store of value
3) a medium of exchange
4) a unit of account
5) an asset
6) a commodity
7) property
8) a protocol
9) a network
10) FREEDOM

This is why #Bitcoin is so misunderstood. It can't and won't ever fit within the confines of our already established, well defined definitions of value. That's because it's nearly ALL value.

- Vì Mỹ là cường quốc kinh tế số 1 thế giới.
- Vì SEC là nhà cái quyền lực số 1 thế giới.

Unpopular fact:

#RealEstate prices will crash in terms of #Bitcoin    until real estate is priced in Bitcoin.

We've been fooled into believing that houses are worth 10x the annual salary because of the utility they provide.

This is a lie that most of society thinks will go on forever.

House prices have been on a tear since 1971 because that's when the US severed the link between gold and USD.

In terms of USD, houses will continue to rise in price forever because buyers need to make up for the interest they pay on their mortgage.

Home prices doubled, or in some cases even tripled, since 2011.

They will probably triple in value again in the next 10 years.

A house that cost 100,000 #BTC    12 years ago costs ~11 BTC today.

A house that costs ~11 BTC today will likely cost less than 2 BTC within the next 10 years.

That's a 99% price reduction in terms of BTC, but a 100-200% price increase in terms of USD.

Most people will ignore this.

All I can say is:

STUDY BITCOIN.

That's how many times #Bitcoin has reached the extremely low volatility zone in its 14 years of price action.

It happened for the first time in 4 years in September 2023.

The rise to 38k seems substantial, but remember what it took to get here.

We've effectively seen sideways price action for 8 months of 2023, and this is just the first rise after the fact.

It's not up only, but these low volatility phases bring the most powerful moves of the mid-cycle, that seem not to make sense.

After these moves, it has always been a jump to the 73 high volatility line, with higher prices alongside it.

Our volatility is still crazy low on this metric... being overly bearish will hurt big time!

cleaned_data.original_text:
Not even Quantum computers will be able to defeat #Bitcoin and the literal #BTC network

hear me out, 

Quantum computing represents a fundamental leap from traditional computing,

Unlike classical computers, 

which process information in bits (0s or 1s), quantum computers use quantum bits or qubits. Qubits, 

Through the principles of superposition and entanglement, can hold and process a vast amount of information more efficiently than classical bits. 

This efficiency makes quantum computers particularly adept at solving certain types of problems much faster than classical computers.

Now, 

relating this to #Bitcoin,

BTC's security largely hinges on cryptographic algorithms like SHA-256 for hashing and the Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm (ECDSA) for wallet security. 

Classical computers, even the most powerful, would require impractical amounts of time to break these algorithms. 

but, a sufficiently powerful quantum computer could, in theory, solve these problems much more "rapidly."

in theory. 

Particularly, 

"Shor's algorithm" in quantum computing poses a theoretical threat to ECDSA, potentially enabling the derivation of private keys from public keys.

I fundamentally disagree with the overstated fears around quantum computing's threat to #Bitcoin. 

There are several key arguments to consider:

Practicality and Timeframe,

The current state of quantum computing is far from being able to threaten Bitcoin. 

The largest quantum computers today are still experimental and nowhere near the number of qubits required to break Bitcoin's cryptography. 

This development is likely decades away, giving the Bitcoin community ample time to implement post-quantum cryptographic algorithms.

Network Consensus and Adaptation,

Any changes to Bitcoin's cryptographic algorithms would require network consensus, 

which is a cornerstone of Bitcoin's decentralized ethos. 

This consensus-driven approach means the community is unlikely to let Bitcoin become vulnerable to quantum attacks.

Misplaced Priorities,

The worry about quantum computing breaking Bitcoin's cryptography often misses a larger point. 

If quantum computing reaches such an advanced stage, 

#Bitcoin will not be the only technology at risk. 

The entire fabric of digital security, including banking, national security, and internet privacy, would be in jeopardy. 

In such a scenario, #Bitcoin's vulnerability would be part of a much larger crisis.

For every measure there is a countermeasure taking place, always remember this. 

#Bitcoin has a substantial economic backing and community. 

This support system provides strong incentives to maintain the network's security against all types of threats, including quantum computing.

The narrative that quantum computing will "break" #Bitcoin fails to account for the dynamic and resilient nature of Bitcoin's technology and community.

Another model has also turned a new "blue" leaf, BitTime.

According to this model, #Bitcoin will follow a cycle very close to cycle 2 (2015 - 2018).

The Black Cycles (1 and 3) proved just how close this can be... with all significant dates lining up to the month.

The double top was written in the books for 2021 according to 2013.

We shouldn't expect Bitcoin to do exactly as it did in 2015 - 2018... that would make it too easy.

At this point in 2015, Bitcoin was rising into December. Will we see the same again?

Even if there is a correction from this exact point, it doesn't seem our larger move is complete for the next few months.

Another sideways period is scheduled after the completion of this rise, standard for each cycle.

The next early top (purple dot) should come in June with a placeholder estimate of 47k.

The bottom from that rise should be in August according to the previous white cycle.

Assuming the white cycle performance is correct, there will be a singular top in December 2025. My estimated price is 90 - 130k with favor to the higher end.

Un top sur #BTC à 148 700 $ 🚀

Ce qui est fascinant avec les derniers cycles sur #Bitcoin, c’est que pendant la période du bear market, il y a 21 barres qui s’écoulent (+/- 21 jours). Et pendant la période de bull market, ce sont 51 barres qui s’écoulent (+/- 21 jours).

Je remarque que si je trace une courbe qui relie tous les sommets entre eux, lorsque je touche la 51ème barre du bull market de 2024-2025, cela me donne un prix de 148 700 $ le 27 octobre 2025 📈.

Le plus fou, c’est que ce point coïncide avec le niveau des 2.618 de Fibonacci 🟢.

Personnellement, je pense que c’est un prix largement atteignable à mon humble avis ✅.

Que pensez-vous de ce top pour le bull run qui arrive, mes amis ? Je suis curieux de savoir ??

🚨Bitcoin and Crypto Market Updates 🚨

$BTC continues to consolidate in the trend channel I shared earlier since Oct, it seems like it's now also creating a pattern that has a much higher probability of breaking to the upside than the downside (check how many times the green resistance is hit, the more it hits, the higher the chance of a break to the upside). Usually after these kind of long consolidations, the "move" that happens is a BIG move! Can it still crash to the downside? yes, but probability wise, this pattern breaks more to the upside than downside, and in some cases, it does a fake out and then reverses. 

 Two more days till Nov monthly candle closes! Next 4 months, any "dips" will be buying opportunities and we will have to keep our eyes and ears open for upcoming major launches!

cleaned_data.original_text:
What's Next for $BTC | Bitcoin Analysis

Bitcoin is struggling at $34,500; what lies ahead?

Bitcoin started out on a strong note the week, but the excitement quickly gave way to disappointment. So far, this is a failed breakout for BTC. 

Technical analysis

Following the consolidation period in the bullish pennant, BTC broke out to the upside and quickly retested the $36,000 area before immediately rejecting. 

BTC is now back below the $34,500 horizontal resistance that you’d have liked to see flip into new support. Long story short, BTC is currently struggling at this level.

We may see some support around the $33,300 level. However, the more major support to the downside is the $31,300 to $31,500 zone.

RSI and funding rates

Bitcoin’s RSI on the daily timeframe has now reset somewhat and is no longer in overbought territory. If the bearish divergence fully plays out, this would likely see BTC test the low $33k.

The funding rate is still positive, but it has pulled back substantially overnight on the BTC move down from $35,300 to $34,300 (current price). 

We saw yesterday how the funding rate was extremely positive, and open interest was high, which we said showed an overheated derivatives market, which is usually not positive for price, which has played out over the past 24 hours.

This funding rate has reset somewhat, and open Interest has come down a tad but not too heavily - so there remains a lot of leverage which could see the door opened for the price to flush lower again.

Cryptonary’s take

We were right yesterday when we recommended caution in our analysis. A failed breakout is usually never a good thing, and price usually continues lower. We also had an overheated derivatives market and a major bearish divergence on the RSI.

We feel a move back to $35,500 may be on the cards. But considering the rejection of the breakout, the odds favour a more meaningful pullback to at least $33,300.

However, it’s hard to have a strong conviction. Therefore, on a zoomed-out timeframe, we’d be DCA buying sub $32,000 for BTC.

Action

We are not taking any action here. However, we will be buyers of BTC sub $32,000.

100 BPS: 60,000 blocks.

Let's make some more noise @KaspaCurrency and the community.

cleaned_data.original_text:
Why would anyone buy an ETF when they can simply buy spot #BTC and take it into self-custody? 

Technically any individual should be able to buy spot BTC and lock it away in cold storage. But the reality is that many people have their investment money sitting with a trusted financial advisor (FA). 

FA’s work for regulated financial institutions such as Morgan Stanley, UBS, Charles Schwab, Etc. These firms are only permitted to invest their clients’ money in publicly traded stocks, bonds or funds. Buying spot #BTC for clients isn’t even an option for these folks. 

Why are ETFs such a big deal? Because FAs and RIAs (registered investment advisors) manage more than $30 trillion in client assets!!

The launch of spot Bitcoin ETFs will unleash an ocean of latent demand for exposure to BTC, the best performing asset of the last decade which is now (with Uncle Larry’s blessing) considered a flight to quality. 

Of course Bitcoiners have known that BTC is a flight to quality this entire time. But Wall Street and Main Street are just now recognizing this fact. 

ETFs remove the shackles and allow these clients to have exposure to Bitcoin without the need to a) worry about how to buy BTC on some crypto exchange, or b) worry about how to safely custody their clients’ BTC once it has been acquired or c), worry about how to help the client to leverage their BTC as collateral or d) worry about how to integrate their clients BTC holdings into their enterprise software systems. 

With the spot ETF, all four of these concerns are vaporized. They’ll be able to buy BTC using the same exchanges they use to buy and sell assets for their clients currently. They’ll be able to custody the ETF shares with the same custodians who custody their assets today. FAs will be able to facilitate loans against their ETF shares the way they enable clients to borrow against their stock and bond portfolios. And their clients’ BTC holdings will be seamlessly integrated into their existing enterprise software because they’re just shares like any other ETF. 

Crypto bros wonder why anyone would accept a custodial form of BTC when non custodial BTC is available?

What many fail to understand is that regular Main Street plebs don’t want self custody. It’s much more of a hassle to them than simply leaving the assets on an exchange or in the possession of a trusted custodian. 

They are not like us. We are the early adopters. These folks are the early and late majority who represent an entirely different and much larger demographic than us early adopters here on crypto X. Giving them a product that works for them is critical to going mainstream. 

With this context in mind, perhaps now you better understand why there’s so much excitement over the spot #Bitcoin ETFs.

That’s right, EVERYONE.

If anyone remembers "V for Vendetta," 

Themes of freedom, oppression, and the use of masks to represent the idea of unifying under a common cause without the necessity of a central figure,

#Bitcoin particularly in the context of financial sovereignty and the disruption of centralized control.

V's mask becomes a symbol of rebellion against an authoritarian regime, a tool for citizens to join a movement anonymously, fighting for their liberty without fear of individual persecution. 

#Bitcoin, which is built on the principles of pseudonymity and decentralization. 

Just as V's mask allows individuals to adopt a new identity that stands for freedom, 

#Bitcoin enables users to perform financial transactions without the need for a central authority, empowering them to transact and store wealth freely.

#Bitcoin can be perceived as a digital manifestation of V's ideals, 

Fighting against financial oppression and censorship from central banks and governments, much like V battles the tyrannical control of the Norsefire party. 

#Bitcoin as an idea, stands for the dissolution of absolute power from traditional financial institutions. 

V's strategy to dismantle the oppressive structures of his world involves educating the population and inspiring them to take ownership of their future. 

V saw no room for compromise in his mission, there is no middle ground when it comes to financial freedom and privacy. 

#Bitcoin is not just an alternative financial system; it is the only true path to achieving financial autonomy and disrupting the status quo. 

There is no reforming them; there is only the absolute solution of replacing them with a system where power is returned to the individual.

#Bitcoin does not merely align with the concepts presented in "V for Vendetta"; it embodies the struggle for freedom in the digital age. 

#Bitcoin is the mask that millions can wear to protect themselves from financial tyranny, and the sword with which they can strike against the chains of centralized control.

cleaned_data.original_text:
I've said throughout the bear market that launchpads will pump as we head into the bull run.

And SFUND is pumping hard right now. It's up 70% in a month 👀

Why? Because it is a gamefi launchpad and in my opinion, crypto gaming pumps hard this bull run 🚀

In case you don't know, launchpads allow you to buy into tokens pre-sale, which means you buy new tokens at a discounted rate before launch.

But there's a catch. There's always a catch. To get into launches pre-sale you need to hold $SFUND. The more of the token you hold, the more you are allocated pre-sale in a launch. 

The minimum number of tokens you need to hold with Seedify is 500 and depending on how much you hold your allocation on launches ranges from $10 to $3k.

$10 allocation doesn't sound like much but it adds up. A lot of projects did over a 2x this year, one did a 40x return at its ATH and is currently 6x.

But in 2021 many did over 20x at peak and one did almost a 700x, which is crazy.

This is why I always say. Buy launchpads in a bear market when nobody wants them.

But one thing you need to note is that as an early investor, you are vested, meaning you do not get all your tokens right away. Generally, you get 10% to 20% and the rest is unlocked gradually over several months.

The point of this tweet is not to tell you to go out and blindly ape into SFUND. Not at all!!

I am keeping you guys up to date on my launchpad strategy.

So, why is Seedify pumping? For one, it's the best-performing launchpad of 2023, by a long shot.

And they give you 7 days from launch to get a refund on any pre-sale investment. So, if the launch sucks you can get out.

The important thing about launchpads is you can make money from both the launchpad token and from the launches it gives you access to. 

So in your research, you need to weigh up the cost of the token, how much you think you can earn by holding the token in a bull run, and how much you think you can earn from the launches!

Do your own research and keep your calculations conservative i.e. I wouldn't bet on a 700x launch like 2021 but I would assume a few 50x launches peak bull run.

Also, factor vesting into your calculations. This is vital.

Launchpads were a huge part of my strategy last run and they performed very well for me. So my strategy hasn't changed.

for one, it's the best-performing launchpad of 2023, by a long shot. and they give you 7 days from launch to get a refund on any pre-sale investment. so, if the launch sucks you can get out. the important thing about launchpads is you can make money from both the launchpad token and from the launches it gives you access to. so in your research, you need to weigh up the cost of the token, how much you think you can earn by holding the token in a bull run, and how much you think you can earn from the launches! do your own research and keep your calculations conservative i.e. i wouldn't bet on a 700x launch like 2021 but i would assume a few 50x launches peak bull run. also, factor vesting into your calculations. this is vital. launchpads were a huge part of my strategy last run and they performed very well for me. so my strategy hasn't changed.

cleaned_data.original_text:
You can make a very strong argument for why #BTC returns will continue to diminish during each subsequent cycle, especially when comparing against the returns of the first few cycles with the price of BTC starting from $0. This is perfectly logical. I take no issue with it. 

However, there are also very compelling arguments to be made for why returns will begin to accelerate again, both in nominal and in percentage terms. Let's put some math behind the argument to better illustrate the point. 👇

During the last cycle, we saw a low of about $3.5k per #BTC, and a high of $69k per BTC for a total of 19.7x from trough to peak. 

In order for BTC to outperform its last cycle, it would have to increase from its cycle low of $16,000 to a high of $320,000 per coin. The market cap would have to grow from $300 billion, to a network value of $6.7 trillion. 

Is this really an insurmountable task? I don't think so. 

If we use the conservative Bank of America multiplier for BTC of 118x, where the market cap of #BTC tends to increase by $118 for every $1 invested, it would require $58 billion to be invested into BTC during this next cycle in order for Bitcoin to reach a $6.7 trillion market cap, or $320,000 per coin. 

Not only is this possible, it is probable because have reached an inflection point. As mentioned previously, BlackRock alone is anticipating $200 billion of inflows from its existing clients. There's a whole slew of asset managers who will be approved for spot ETFs, and they will also bring tens of billions of dollars into BTC. At the same time, Available Supply is shrinking along with issuance. This trend will be present in this next cycle, and for every cycle after it. More dollars will chase BTC in each cycle, and supply will continue to diminish in each cycle. This would actually increase the multiplier over time. 

The more time rolls on, the more people realize that their central banks are stealing from them, and the less trust they have in fiat money. The rollout of CBDCs and social credit systems will exacerbate this distrust. This will result in more people seeking a form of money that no one can control, increasing the demand for BTC, and decreasing its available supply  even further. 

For these reasons it would be foolish to assume that BTC's best returns are behind it. They very well could be, but this is not an assumption that anyone should take for granted. The supply/demand dynamics suggest that the world is about to experience absolute scarcity for the first time in human history. I suspect it will reshape people's perceptions about how high and how fast BTC can appreciate against failing fiat currencies the world over.
